sql:
SELECT user_id, 0 AS total_deposits
FROM users
WHERE user_id NOT IN (SELECT user_id FROM investments);

SELECT notification_id
FROM notifications
WHERE user_id = 1 AND status = 'sent';

external_knowledge:
- "sprouted from fertile ground" refers to listings with a high ROI;
- "golden promises" and "fivefold harvest" refer to the ROI field in listings, where ROI > 5;
- "sowing dates" refer to the investment_date of investments made in the last 7 days;
- "seeds planted" refers to the amount_invested;
- "gardeners of fortune" metaphorically represent the users who have invested in these listings.

sql:
SELECT users.user_id, users.username
FROM users
INNER JOIN listing_updates ON users.user_id = listing_updates.updated_by;

external_knowledge:
- "rays of sunshine" metaphorically refers to active users who are engaged in investments; 
- "glowing messages" represents active notifications in correspondence with these users; 
- "brightly shining" is a metaphor for the status of 'active' for both the investments and the notifications.

'folks' refers to users in the system;
'put money into' means invested in the listings;
'active listings' refers to listings that are not in 'paused' status.

- Risky ventures refer to HYIP listings;
- Safer options refer to bonds listings;
- Active participants refer to users with an 'active' status.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_active_listings, AVG(CAST(REPLACE(roi, '%', '') AS REAL) / 100) AS average_roi
FROM listings
WHERE status = 'active';
